00:11:34,210 --> 00:11:36,212
I'LL DO WHAT I CAN, BOBBY.
I'D APPRECIATE IT.
I DO.

198
00:11:36,212 --> 00:11:39,215
ALL RIGHT.  GOOD LUCK.
I'M GONNA TAKE CARE
OF THIS.  THANK YOU.

199
00:11:56,232 --> 00:11:58,234
[ Buzzing ]

200
00:12:00,736 --> 00:12:03,739
[ Buzzing ]

201
00:12:06,242 --> 00:12:08,411
CAN YOU JUST
CALM DOWN A MINUTE ?

202
00:12:09,912 --> 00:12:12,415
YOU'RE GONNA GET
THE MONEY.

203
00:12:12,915 --> 00:12:15,418
HOW DO I KNOW ?

204
00:12:15,418 --> 00:12:17,420
YOU HAVE MY WORD.
IS THAT ENOUGH ?

205
00:12:19,922 --> 00:12:22,425
YOU KNOW,
 YOU TALK TOO MUCH.

206
00:12:22,425 --> 00:12:24,927
GET OFF THE FUCKIN' PHONE.
I LOVE YA !

207
00:12:24,927 --> 00:12:27,930
GO--  ALL RIGHT.
G-GOOD-BYE.

208
00:12:28,931 --> 00:12:30,933
[ Chuckling ]

209
00:12:32,935 --> 00:12:34,937
I'M TELLIN' YA--

210
00:12:40,443 --> 00:12:43,446
YOU LIKE THE PONIES ?

211
00:12:43,446 --> 00:12:45,948
YEAH, SURE.
YOU BET PONIES ?

212
00:12:45,948 --> 00:12:47,950
YE--  N-NO.
NOT REALLY.

213
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:50,953
OH, SMART.  THEY'RE HARD
AS HELL TO HANDICAP.

214
00:12:50,953 --> 00:12:54,457
YOU KNOW WHAT
I LIKE ?  JAI ALAI.

215
00:12:54,457 --> 00:12:57,960
WITH THE--
YEAH.  YOU KNOW
WHY I LIKE IT ?

216
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,962
IT'S FIXED.

217
00:12:59,962 --> 00:13:02,465
SURE THING.  THAT'S
THE ONLY WAY TO WIN.

218
00:13:02,965 --> 00:13:04,967
YOU SEE
THAT HORSE THERE ?

219
00:13:06,969 --> 00:13:09,472
THE BLAZE.
THIS ONE.
THIS ONE HERE ?

220
00:13:09,472 --> 00:13:11,974
YEAH, YEAH.  I BOUGHT
THE HORSE IN '66.

221
00:13:11,974 --> 00:13:14,477
I HIRED A TRAINER,
STALL, WHATEVER.

222
00:13:14,477 --> 00:13:16,979
THAT HORSE
MADE ME $100,000.

223
00:13:16,979 --> 00:13:19,482
IN SIXTIES DOLLARS
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT IS ?

224
00:13:19,482 --> 00:13:22,485
YEAH, IT'S, UH--  YEAH.
IT'S A LOT OF MONEY.
A MILLION, EASY.

225
00:13:22,985 --> 00:13:25,488
A LOT OF MONEY, YEAH.
MUST HAVE BEEN
SOME FAST HORSE.

226
00:13:25,488 --> 00:13:28,491
IT NEVER WON A RACE.

227
00:13:28,491 --> 00:13:30,993
IT GOT ME IN GOOD
WITH THE TRAINER.
SIT DOWN.

228
00:13:34,997 --> 00:13:37,500
ATTABOY.

229
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,502
YEAH, THE TRAINER AND I,
WE HAD A THING.

230
00:13:39,502 --> 00:13:42,004
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT IT WAS.
SOME FUCKIN' THING.

231
00:13:42,004 --> 00:13:45,508
THE JOCKEY WOULD RAISE
 THE FUCKIN' WHIP...

232
00:13:46,008 --> 00:13:48,511
AND WHATEVER
THE FUCK IT WAS.

233
00:13:48,511 --> 00:13:51,514
WE HAD A GOOD THING.
BUT, YOU KNOW, THIS ONE
TELLS THAT ONE.

234
00:13:51,514 --> 00:13:54,016
THE OTHER ONE
TELLS ANOTHER ONE,
AND BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,

235
00:13:54,016 --> 00:13:56,018
THE WHOLE WORLD,
EVERYBODY'S IN ON IT.

236
00:13:58,020 --> 00:14:00,022
THAT'S WHAT YOU CALL
THE SMART MONEY, RIGHT ?

237
00:14:01,524 --> 00:14:03,526
YEAH, YEAH, THAT'S--
[ Chuckles ]

238
00:14:03,526 --> 00:14:06,529
YEAH,
THAT'S THE SMART MONEY.

239
00:14:06,529 --> 00:14:09,031
BOBBY, I LIKE YOU.

240
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:13,536
WHY DO YOU MAKE IT SO HARD
FOR ME TO TAKE CARE OF YOU ?

241
00:14:13,536 --> 00:14:16,539
MAX, I SWEAR TO GOD,
THESE GUYS WERE OUTTA LINE.

242
00:14:16,539 --> 00:14:19,542
NO, NO.  YOU KNOW,
MAYBE LAST TIME
WITH THE PUERTO RICANS.

243
00:14:19,542 --> 00:14:22,545
THESE WERE NICE
JEWISH BOYS.
THEY WERE OUTTA LINE.

244
00:14:22,545 --> 00:14:26,048
BOBBY, I LOVE JESSICA JUST LIKE
SHE'S MY FLESH AND BLOOD.

245
00:14:26,048 --> 00:14:29,552
I WOULD KILL ANYONE
IF THEY AS MUCH AS LAID
A FINGER ON HER...

246
00:14:29,552 --> 00:14:31,554
OR HER BEAUTIFUL DAUGHTER.

247
00:14:32,054 --> 00:14:35,558
BUT THAT FUCKIN'PISHER
THAT YOU SOCKED
IN THE TEETH...

248
00:14:35,558 --> 00:14:41,564
HAS THE MOST EXPENSIVE DENTIST
IN BEVERLY HILLS, WANTS I SHOULD
BUY HIM AN IMPLANT.

249
00:14:41,564 --> 00:14:46,068
YOUR GORILLA HORSESHIT
COST ME EIGHT GRAND.
OKAY.

250
00:14:46,068 --> 00:14:48,070
IF IT'S MONEY,
I'LL WORK IT OFF.

251
00:14:48,571 --> 00:14:51,574
YOU KNOW I'M GOOD
FOR IT.
NOT DRIVIN' JESSICA,
YOU WON'T.

252
00:14:53,576 --> 00:14:56,078
WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT ?
TWO STRIKES,
BOBBY.

253
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,583
AND THE SECOND ONE
WAS BIG.

254
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:03,085
THE BACHELOR'S FATHER,
HE BELONGS TO MY SHUL.

255
00:15:05,588 --> 00:15:07,590
SO... WHAT ?  THAT'S IT ?

256
00:15:08,090 --> 00:15:10,092
I'M OUT.
IT'S OVER.

257
00:15:10,092 --> 00:15:12,595
DID I SAY THAT ?
NO.  I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT DO YOU--

258
00:15:12,595 --> 00:15:15,097
I'M SAYIN' IT'S MY FAULT.

259
00:15:15,598 --> 00:15:19,602
I'M SENDIN' YOU OUT
TO WATCH SCUM DROOL OVER
THE LOVE OF YOUR LIFE,

260
00:15:19,602 --> 00:15:21,604
AND THEN I WONDER
WHY YOU SEE RED ?

261
00:15:21,604 --> 00:15:25,107
IT'S MY FAULT.
THE TOOTH IS ON ME,
BUT NO MORE.

262
00:15:26,108 --> 00:15:29,612
- I'M REASSIGNIN' YOU.
- UH--  N-NO, NO.

263
00:15:29,612 --> 00:15:31,614
I DON'T WANNA DRIVE
ANOTHER GIRL.

264
00:15:31,614 --> 00:15:33,616
THE ONLY REASON I'M WORKIN' HERE
IS BECAUSE I WANNA BE AROUND--

265
00:15:34,116 --> 00:15:36,619
HEY, IS THIS
A FUCKIN' DEMOCRACY ?

266
00:15:36,619 --> 00:15:40,122
WHO THE FUCK DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKIN' TO ?

267
00:15:40,122 --> 00:15:42,124
YOU WANT OUT ?

268
00:15:42,124 --> 00:15:45,127
DO I PUT FOOD
ON YOUR TABLE ?

269
00:15:45,127 --> 00:15:49,632
I SPONSOR YOUR TRAINING.
I TAKE CARE OF YOUR GIRL
AND HER LITTLE BABY.

270
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:53,636
I EVEN PAY FOR THAT
DEADBEAT FRIEND OF YOURS...

271
00:15:53,636 --> 00:15:55,638
FOR PUSHIN' A GODDAMN BROOM.

272
00:15:56,138 --> 00:16:01,143
YEAH, YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
SO ARE YOU READY
TO SIT DOWN AND LISTEN ?

273
00:16:01,143 --> 00:16:03,646
SIT DOWN !

274
00:16:03,646 --> 00:16:05,648
SIT DOWN AND HEAR !

275
00:16:08,651 --> 00:16:11,153
CAN YOU HEAR NOW ?
YEAH.

276
00:16:13,155 --> 00:16:16,158
I THINK I GOT SOMETHIN'
THAT'LL MAKE EVERYBODY HAPPY.

277
00:16:16,158 --> 00:16:19,161
I WORK WITH A GUY
NAMED RUIZ.

278
00:16:19,161 --> 00:16:21,163
I WANT YOU
TO GO WITH HIM,

279
00:16:21,163 --> 00:16:23,666
ACCOMPANY HIM
ON A DROP.

280
00:16:23,666 --> 00:16:25,668
HE'S GOT HIS OWN MEN.
YOU'RE JUST SCENERY.

281
00:16:25,668 --> 00:16:29,672
I WANT A BIG GUINEA
WITH A BUSTED FACE
HANGIN' AROUND AS A DETERRENT.

282
00:16:29,672 --> 00:16:32,675
YOU GO,
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

283
00:16:32,675 --> 00:16:34,677
AND WE'RE SQUARE
ON THE TOOTH.

284
00:16:34,677 --> 00:16:37,680
I--  IT--
WHAT ABOUT RICKY ?

285
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,682
HE WOULD JUMP
AT AN OPPORTUNITY
TO DO THIS.

286
00:16:40,182 --> 00:16:44,186
RICKY ?  RICKY
"I LOST THE TRUCK" RICKY ?

287
00:16:45,688 --> 00:16:48,691
I--  YOU SAID YOU LIKED HIM.
YOU WANTED TO WORK WITH HIM.

288
00:16:48,691 --> 00:16:52,194
THAT WAS BEFORE HE LOST
MY CARPET-CLEANING VAN.

289
00:16:53,195 --> 00:16:55,698
OKAY.  LET ME TALK TO HIM.
HE'LL WORK IT OFF.

290
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,702
JESUS.  YOU KNOW,
I DON'T KNOW THE KID.

291
00:16:59,702 --> 00:17:02,204
THE LITTLE THAT I KNOW
ABOUT HIM SCARES ME.

292
00:17:02,204 --> 00:17:04,707
I GREW UP WITH HIM.
HE'S A GOOD GUY.

293
00:17:04,707 --> 00:17:08,210
UH-HUH.  WELL,
YOU VOUCH FOR HIM ?

294
00:17:08,210 --> 00:17:11,213
[ Muttering ]
I-I-I GREW UP WITH THE GUY.
UH-HUH.

295
00:17:11,213 --> 00:17:13,716
YOU VOUCH FOR HIM ?

296
00:17:13,716 --> 00:17:16,719
DO I--
YOU MEAN, DO I--
DO YOU VOUCH FOR HIM ?

297
00:17:19,221 --> 00:17:23,726
UM, HE--  YEAH.
YEAH, OF COURSE I VOUCH FOR HIM.

298
00:17:23,726 --> 00:17:26,228
HOW ABOUT THIS ?

299
00:17:26,228 --> 00:17:28,230
YOU'RE IN, HE'S IN.

300
00:17:28,731 --> 00:17:30,733
I DON'T--

301
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:34,236
YOU'RE BEATIN' PEOPLE UP.
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
GET PAID FOR IT.

302
00:17:35,237 --> 00:17:37,239
THINK ABOUT IT.

303
00:17:37,239 --> 00:17:42,244
YOU GOTTA TAKE THAT GUY OUT.
YOU OWN THAT GUY.
YOU OWN HIM.  COME ON !

304
00:17:42,244 --> 00:17:44,246
WE NEED GUNS.
HE DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING ABOUT GUNS.

305
00:17:44,246 --> 00:17:46,248
HE IMPLIED SOMETHING
ABOUT GUNS, I'M SURE.

306
00:17:46,248 --> 00:17:49,251
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
YOU IMPLY.  IT'S SOMETHING
YOU LAY OUT ON THE TABLE.

307
00:17:49,251 --> 00:17:52,254
HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT GUNS.  BESIDES,
I'M NOT TAKING THE JOB.

308
00:17:52,755 --> 00:17:54,757
IT'S THE OPPORTUNITY
OF A LIFETIME, BOBBY.
YOU NUTS ?

309
00:17:54,757 --> 00:17:57,259
YOU'VE BEEN WAITING
FOR THIS OPPORTUNITY.

310
00:17:57,259 --> 00:18:00,262
NO,YOU'VEBEEN WAITING
FOR THIS OPPORTUNITY.
YOU'RE DAMN STRAIGHT.

311
00:18:00,262 --> 00:18:02,264
YOU THINK I LIKE LIVIN'
ON FUCKIN' YUCCA ?

312
00:18:02,264 --> 00:18:04,767
[ Ricky ]  YOU DO GOOD
ON SOMETHING LIKE THIS,
AND THEN YOU'RE IN.

313
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:06,769
YOU HAVE OPPORTUNITIES
AFTER THAT.
WHAT ABOUT BOXING ?

314
00:18:06,769 --> 00:18:08,771
BOBBY, YOU'RE OUTTA
YOUR MIND.
OH, YOU'RE FULL OF SHIT.

315
00:18:08,771 --> 00:18:11,774
I CLOWNED WITH YOU
FOR TWO FUCKIN' ROUNDS,
DID THIS SHIT.
OH, STOP.

316
00:18:11,774 --> 00:18:14,276
IT WAS A FUCKIN' DRAW.
I DIDN'T TRAIN FOR THE FIGHT !
THAT WAS HORSESHIT !

317
00:18:14,276 --> 00:18:16,779
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE
A PROFESSIONAL BOXER !
LET'S DO IT RIGHT NOW.

318
00:18:17,279 --> 00:18:19,281
I'M NOT TALKIN'
ABOUT FIGHTING.
YOU'LL NEVER BE A BOXER.

319
00:18:19,281 --> 00:18:21,784
COME ON.  RIGHT NOW.
DON'T START FUCKIN' PUSHIN' ME.
FUCK YOU, MAN !

320
00:18:22,284 --> 00:18:24,787
LET'S DO IT.
DON'T BE A FUCKIN' CHILD.
 DON'T BE A FUCKIN' CHILD !

321
00:18:24,787 --> 00:18:27,790
[ Man ]  RICKY !  BOBBY !
CUT THAT SHIT OUT !
[ Both ]  SORRY, COACH.

322
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:30,793
HOW'S THE BOXING GOING ?

323
00:18:30,793 --> 00:18:34,296
REALLY GOOD, COACH.
YEAH, REALLY GOOD.
HE'S FIVE, FIVE AND ONE.

324
00:18:34,296 --> 00:18:36,799
STICK WITH IT, BOBBY.
YOU KNOW IT TAKES TIME.

325
00:18:37,299 --> 00:18:39,301
YOU ALWAYS HAD
THE HEART.

326
00:18:39,301 --> 00:18:42,304
[ Ricky ]
HOW 'BOUT ME, COACH ?
DID I ALWAYS HAVE HEART ?

327
00:18:43,305 --> 00:18:45,307
WHAT ARE YOU
GAWKIN' AT, LADIES ?

328
00:18:45,808 --> 00:18:47,810
THIS IS NOT RECESS.
[ Blows Whistle ]

329
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:49,812
[ Coach ]
RUN A PLAY.
LET'S RUN A PLAY.

330
00:18:49,812 --> 00:18:53,315
FUCK HIM.  YOU'D THINK
HE'D LET IT GO AFTER A WHILE.

331
00:18:53,315 --> 00:18:57,319
THE FACT IS WE PROBABLY
COULD'VE BEAT FAIRFAX
IF YOU HADN'T GOT SUSPENDED.

332
00:18:57,319 --> 00:18:59,822
WHATEVER, MAN.
FUCKIN' ASSHOLE.

333
00:18:59,822 --> 00:19:01,824
I MEAN, T-SHIRTS ?
REALLY.
I LIKED THOSE SHIRTS.

334
00:19:01,824 --> 00:19:03,826
YOU NEVER WORE
THOSE SHIRTS ?
WE COULD HAVE BOUGHT THEM.

335
00:19:03,826 --> 00:19:05,828
I ALMOST GOT SUSPENDED
OVER THAT SHIT.

336
00:19:05,828 --> 00:19:09,832
THANK GOD YOU TOOK THE BULLET
FOR ME AND DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.
I APPRECIATE IT.

337
00:19:09,832 --> 00:19:12,835
WANT A HIT ?
NAH, MAN, I GOTTA
PICK UP THE BABY.

338
00:19:12,835 --> 00:19:15,838
WHY YOU ALWAYS GET STUCK
PICKIN' UP THE KID ?
I LIKE IT, OKAY ?

339
00:19:15,838 --> 00:19:19,341
IT'S NOT EVEN YOUR KID.
YOU WANT A LIFT, OR YOU
WANNA STAY HERE AND WALK ?

340
00:19:19,341 --> 00:19:21,343
[ Woman ]
THAT LOOKS GREAT.

341
00:19:21,343 --> 00:19:25,347
I DON'T KNOW WHY WE DON'T
GET A DRINK INSTEAD OF
SITTIN' INSIDE THIS PLACE.

342
00:19:25,347 --> 00:19:27,850
[ Bobby ]
I PROMISED CHLOE
WE'D COME HERE.

343
00:19:28,851 --> 00:19:31,353
SHE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE SHE IS, BOB.

344
00:19:31,353 --> 00:19:33,355
SHE'D HAVE MORE FUN
IF WE WERE AT BOARDNER'S.

345
00:19:33,856 --> 00:19:37,359
SHE COULD PLAY
THE TRIVIA GAME OR THE LITTLE
RACING GAME THING SHE DOES.

346
00:19:37,359 --> 00:19:40,362
SHE'S A LITTLE GIRL.
LITTLE GIRLS DON'T LIKE
TO GO TO BARS.

347
00:19:40,362 --> 00:19:42,364
WE HAD FUN.
WE WENT TO BARS
WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

348
00:19:42,364 --> 00:19:44,867
AND ALL THE DIFFERENT PEOPLE,
RIGHT ?  REMEMBER SLIMMY ?

349
00:19:44,867 --> 00:19:48,370
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
THERE'S NO SMOKING
ALLOWED IN THE STORE.

350
00:19:48,871 --> 00:19:52,374
WHY, YOU SERVING FOOD ?
NO, IT'S STORE POLICY.

351
00:19:52,374 --> 00:19:54,376
AND YOU CAN'T SIT
AT A STATION UNLESS
YOU PURCHASE A CERAMIC.

352
00:19:54,877 --> 00:19:58,881
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS SHIT ?
I CAN'T SIT AT A STATION
WITHOUT PURCHASING A CERAMIC ?

353
00:19:58,881 --> 00:20:00,883
WHY DON'T YOU BRING ME
AN ASHTRAY, THEN ?

354
00:20:00,883 --> 00:20:04,386
CAN I COLOR ME THAT,
A CERAMIC ASHTRAY ?
RIGHT AWAY.

355
00:20:07,389 --> 00:20:09,892
AND WHAT COLOR PAINTS
CAN I GET YOU ?
I DON'T KNOW.

356
00:20:09,892 --> 00:20:14,396
SURPRISE ME.
I'M NOT SURE WHAT
I'M FEELING TODAY.

357
00:20:14,897 --> 00:20:17,399
NOW, LISTEN TO ME.

358
00:20:17,399 --> 00:20:20,903
I THINK MAXIE'S STARTING
TO REACH OUT TO YOU
WITH THIS THING,

359
00:20:20,903 --> 00:20:22,905
AND IT'S NOT SOMETHING
THAT YOU SHOULD LET SLIP BY.

360
00:20:22,905 --> 00:20:24,907
WHAT'S WRONG, BABY ?
HE'S NOT DOING IT.

361
00:20:24,907 --> 00:20:26,909
WHAT IS
SHE SAYING ?
HE'S NOT PAINTING.

362
00:20:26,909 --> 00:20:29,912
-I'M GONNA PAINT
 WHEN I GET MY PAINTS.
- THERE YOU GO.

363
00:20:31,914 --> 00:20:35,417
THERE'S A NICE WAY
TO DO THAT.
WILL YOU PAINT ?

364
00:20:35,417 --> 00:20:38,420
MAXIE WON'T LET ME DRIVE JESS
ANYMORE.
WHO'S HE HAVE
DRIVIN' HER ?

365
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:41,423
I DON'T KNOW.  I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HE'S GOT GOIN' ON.

366
00:20:41,423 --> 00:20:43,926
- ISN'T IT FUN ?
- WHAT'S THAT, SWEETIE ?

367
00:20:43,926 --> 00:20:45,928
ISN'T IT FUN ?
WHAT'S THAT ?

368
00:20:45,928 --> 00:20:47,930
ISN'T IT FUN ?
WHAT FUN ?

369
00:20:48,430 --> 00:20:51,433
ISN'T IT FUN TO PAINT ?
TO PAINT ?
YEAH.  I LOVE IT.

370
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:54,937
REALLY CALMS ME DOWN.
FROGS AREN'T PURPLE,
BY THE WAY.

371
00:20:54,937 --> 00:20:57,940
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
A PURPLE FROG ?
YOU HAVE ?

372
00:20:57,940 --> 00:21:00,442
WHEN YOU WERE ASLEEP ?
WHY YOU GIVING HER
A HARD TIME ?

373
00:21:00,442 --> 00:21:02,945
THIS IS A GOOD OPPORTUNITY.
IF WE PLAY THIS RIGHT--

374
00:21:02,945 --> 00:21:05,447
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING.
HE'S A SKETCHY CHARACTER.

375
00:21:05,447 --> 00:21:09,451
I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT HIM
IN FRONT OF THE "ABY-BAY."
OKAY, LET'S DROP IT.

376
00:21:09,451 --> 00:21:11,954
LET'S DROP IT.
LET'S "EX-NAY"
ON THE "BEX-NAY."

377
00:21:11,954 --> 00:21:13,956
"IG-PAY ATIN-LAY."
CAN YOU "UT-SHAY"
YOUR "OUTH-MAY" ?

378
00:21:13,956 --> 00:21:15,958
"AIN-SAYING-AY."
YOU'RE DOING IT WRONG.

379
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,460
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.
"ONCH-PAY OO-BAY."

380
00:21:19,962 --> 00:21:22,464
"AY-BAY,
 AY-WAY."
"AX-MAY"
YOUR "ASS-AY."

381
00:21:22,965 --> 00:21:26,969
"UT-SHAY" YOUR "ACE-FAY,"
"ASSHOLE-AY."

382
00:21:27,469 --> 00:21:30,472
DID YOU HEAR THAT ?
DID YOU HEAR
WHAT HE SAID ?

383
00:21:30,472 --> 00:21:32,975
WHAT DO YOU
THINK OF THAT ?

384
00:21:35,477 --> 00:21:39,197
-HERE YOU GO, SWEETIE.
- I DON'T WANT GRILLED CHEESE.

385
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:42,701
YOU LOVE
GRILLED CHEESE.
I HATE CHEESE.

386
00:21:42,701 --> 00:21:45,704
COME ON, SWEETIE.
MOMMY'S IN A HURRY.
DON'T BE A LITTLE SHIT, OKAY ?

387
00:21:46,204 --> 00:21:47,706
HEY, HON ?
YEAH.

388
00:21:48,206 --> 00:21:49,708
I'LL FIX HER DINNER.
GO GET READY.

